Heading: Proprietary
Note: For example, publisher’s own series ID. Note that <IDTypeName> is required with proprietary identifiers

Heading: ISSN
Note: International Standard Serial Number, unhyphenated, 8 digits

Heading: German Books in Print series ID
DOI
Note: Digital Object Identifier (variable length and character set)

Heading: ISBN-13
Note: Use only where the collection (series or set) is available as a single product

Heading: BNF Control number
Note: French National Bibliography series ID. Identifiant des publications en série maintenu par la Bibliothèque Nationale de France

Heading: ARK
Note: Archival Resource Key, as a URL (including the address of the ARK resolver provided by eg a national library)

Heading: ISSN-L
Note: International Standard Serial Number ‘linking ISSN’, used when distinct from the serial ISSN. Unhyphenated, 8 digits. For use in ONIX 3.0 only
